        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 3:10PM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>At 310 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Terry, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Glendive, Terry, Fallon, West Glendive, Hoyt, Zero, Calypso, Forest
Park, and Marsh.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
